, `.../Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings`, `.../Resources/es.lproj/Localizable.strings`.\n  - Tests: `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/OnboardingPageTests.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (skip onboarding compatibility).\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `Skip onboarding` semantic discoverability; add explicit IDs for step container, step progress, continue, back, skip, strictness info disclosure.\n- `home`\n  - SwiftUI: `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeView.swift`, `HomeViewModel.swift`, `HomeContent.swift`, `MainTabView.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `DSColors.swift`, `DSTypography.swift`, `SAICard.swift`, `SAIButton.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Common.swift`, `L10n+Wake.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift`, `HomeContentTests.swift`, `AppShellSnapshotTests.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests.swift`.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `homeTabRoot`; add `homeNextCommitmentCard`, `homePrimaryActionButton`, `homeViewAllTasksButton`, `homeHistoryPreviewButton`, `homeSyncErrorBanner`, `homeEmptyCreateWakeButton`.\n- `primary_list`\n  - SwiftUI: `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift` (alarms/reliability sections and row actions), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIListRow.swift`, `SAITag.swift`, `DSSectionHeader.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`, `DSColors.swift`.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`, `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (row selectors and resume actions), new UI tests for grouped readiness sections.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve prefix-based IDs `wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeStartRunButton-*`, `wakeEditAlarmButton-*`; add section IDs for `Tonight/Later/Paused` headers and filter/sort controls.\n- `create_edit`\n  - SwiftUI: `WakeDashboardView.swift` (`createAlarmSheet`), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift` (`createAlarm`, `updateAlarm`), potential extracted view `WakeTaskEditorView.swift` (new).\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIButton.swift`, `SAICard.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`, spacing/type tokens.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift` + string resources for linear-step labels and inline validation.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift` (create/update semantics), `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (field+save path), new UI test for validation error persistence.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeAlarmNameField`, `wakeAlarmTimePicker`, `wakeStrictnessPicker`, `wakeFirstTaskField`, `wakeAlarmSaveButton`, `wakeAlarmCancelButton`; add step-indicator and advanced-options IDs.\n- `active_task`\n  - SwiftUI: `WakeDashboardView.swift` (`activeRunSection`), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift` (`triggerAlarm`, `completeMission`, `dismissAlarm`, `completeWakeCheck`, `evaluateEscalationIfNeeded`).\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIButton.swift`, `SAICard.swift`, status/chip components, motion token usage.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift`, `L10n+A11y.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`, `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (mission completion + wake check + first task progression), add reduced-motion and state-banner ordering UI tests.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeRunStateText`, `wakeMissionButton-*`, `wakeDismissAlarmButton`, `wakeCompleteWakeCheckButton`, `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton`; add `wakeFallbackExtraMinuteButton` and `wakeStateBanner` if fallback pattern is introduced.\n- `completion`\n  - SwiftUI: currently within `WakeDashboardView.swift` active-run lifecycle and post-completion list state; likely extract `WakeCompletionView.swift` (new) while preserving `WakeFlowViewModel` completion state.\n  - Assets/tokens: card, success/recovery status components, typography tokens for summary.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift`, `L10n+Common.swift`, strings files for completion outcome copy and next-best action.\n  - Tests: extend `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift` completion assertions; add dedicated UI test for completion panel and recovery CTA in missed/partial outcomes.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton` path; add `wakeCompletionSummary`, `wakeCompletionPrimaryNextAction`, `wakeCompletionRecoveryAction`, `wakeCompletionGoHomeAction`.\n- `history_streaks`\n  - SwiftUI: `WakeDashboardView.swift` (`reliabilitySection`), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift` (`recentRuns`, consistency calculation), potential extracted `WakeHistoryStreaksView.swift` (new).\n  - Assets/tokens: status chips/tags, section headers, chart/summary card components.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift` + new reason-coded labels in strings files.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift` for reason-coded outcomes and trend calculations; new UI tests for time-range filters and visible repair CTA.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeReliabilityRow-*`, `wakeReliabilityEscalatedBadge`, `wakeReliabilityEmptyText`; add `wakeHistoryTrendSummary`, `wakeHistoryTimeRangeControl`, `wakeHistoryRepairAction`.\n- `profile_settings`\n  - SwiftUI: `ProfileView.swift`, `ProfileAccountInfoSection.swift`, `ProfileQuickActionsSection.swift`, `ProfileSubscriptionSection.swift`, `SettingsSubscriptionSection.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIListRow.swift`, `DSSectionHeader.swift`, card/list surface tokens.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Profile.swift`, `L10n+Settings.swift`, `L10n+Payments.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `ProfileViewModelTests.swift`, `PaywallFlowUITests.swift` (profile entry paths), add UI tests for section ordering (`Mission Controls`, `Preferences`, `Account/Billing`, `Help/Legal`).\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `profileTabRoot`, `restorePurchasesButton`, `settingsRestorePurchasesButton`; add IDs for mission controls rows, subscription manage action, legal/help rows, destructive confirmations.\n- `paywall_subscription`\n  - SwiftUI: `Packages/FeatureSettings/.../PaywallView.swift`, `PaywallViewModel.swift`, `SettingsSubscriptionSection.swift`, `ProfileSubscriptionSection.swift`, paywall sheet presentation in `MainTabView.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: button, card, typography, status color tokens.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Payments.swift`, strings files for premium value framing and restore/purchase copy.\n  - Tests: `PaywallViewModelTests.swift`, `PaywallSnapshotTests.swift`, `PaywallFlowUITests.swift`.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `paywallSubscribeButton`, `paywallRestoreButton`, `paywallErrorBanner`, `restorePurchasesButton`; add `paywallPrimaryValueHeader`, `paywallPlanOption-*`, `paywallCloseButton`, `paywallMaybeLaterButton`.\n\n## Expected SwiftUI Components\n- Design token wrappers: `WakeColorTokens`, `WakeTypographyTokens`, `WakeSpacingTokens` adapters over `DSColors`, `DSTypography`, `DSSpacing`.\n- Theme colors: commitment/status palette mapping to `color.action.*` and `color.state.*` semantics.\n- Typography helpers: Dynamic Type-safe title/subtitle/status helpers with tabular numerals for times/streaks.\n- Cards: `NextCommitmentCard`, `WakeTaskCard`, `OutcomeSummaryCard`, `ReliabilityTrendCard`.\n- Rows: `WakeTaskRow`, `HistoryOutcomeRow`, `SettingsActionRow`.\n- Progress/status components: `WakeStepProgress`, `WakeStateBanner`, `ReadinessChip`, `ReliabilityStatusChip`.\n- Primary actions: `WakePrimaryCTA` with one-dominant-action rules for active/completion screens.\n- Empty/error/loading states: reusable `WakeEmptyState`, `WakeInlineErrorBanner`, `WakeScreenSkeleton` wrappers around `SAISkeleton`.\n- Accessibility wrappers: focus-order modifiers, VoiceOver summary builders, reduced-motion alternatives, minimum-hit-target wrappers.\n\n## Tests To Update\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/AppShellSnapshotTests.swift`: assert updated tab metadata and IA labels remain stable.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift`: prove home empty/loading/error/loaded commitment states remain deterministic.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeContentTests.swift`: prove default home quick actions and wake-specific labels align with calm-accountability copy.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/WakeTask/WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`: prove active->dismissed->verified->completed transitions and reason-code outcomes remain correct.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/OnboardingPageTests.swift`: prove onboarding step model and copy/order constraints.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/FeatureSettingsTests/PaywallViewModelTests.swift`: prove offerings load, purchase/restore error paths, and subscription state transitions.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/PaywallSnapshotTests.swift`: prove paywall visual hierarchy and CTA ordering in light/dark and Dynamic Type.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests.swift`: prove launch path still exposes required tabs and root surfaces.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift`: prove critical end-to-end wake flow still automation-reachable with updated identifiers.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/PaywallFlowUITests.swift`: prove paywall open/close/select/subscribe/restore behavior and profile entry paths.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift`: prove onboarding skip and auth transitions still function with revised onboarding controls.\n- `scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`: prove telemetry report still captures visited screens and tapped IDs after identifier updates.\n- Add screenshot-manifest validation test (new, repo-local): prove required before/after screenshot IDs and variants exist in manifest JSON.\n\n## Screenshot States To Capture\n- Current baseline artifact status: real baseline capture is currently blocked in this worker because `xcrun` is unavailable; baseline manifest should be captured in hosted iOS validation environment.\n- Required before/after states per screen (`onboarding`, `home`, `primary_list`, `create_edit`, `active_task`, `completion`, `history_streaks`, `profile_settings`, `paywall_subscription`):\n  - `before/default`\n  - `after/default`\n  - `empty`\n  - `loading`\n  - `error`\n  - `success` (where applicable)\n  - `active_task` live state and fallback state\n  - `completion` success and missed/partial recovery state\n  - `paywall/subscription` free-state paywall, subscribed state, restore error state\n  - Dynamic Type (`AX2` or equivalent large size)\n  - dark mode variant\n- Additional named states from `screen-spec.json` to capture explicitly:\n  - `onboarding`: defaults populated, save/validation error, skip-visible.\n  - `home`: no-commitment empty, sync-failure banner with last-known summary.\n  - `primary_list`: grouped readiness sections (`Tonight`, `Later`, `Paused`) and section-level retry.\n  - `create_edit`: step progress visible, inline field validation, advanced options collapsed/expanded.\n  - `active_task`: single dominant CTA, explicit state banner, safe fallback action.\n  - `completion`: next-best primary action and secondary history/repair options.\n  - `history_streaks`: trend summary with reason-coded outcomes and repair CTA.\n  - `profile_settings`: section ordering mission-first then preferences then account/billing then help/legal.\n  - `paywall_subscription`: contextual premium value framing with non-blocking dismissal.\n\n## Appium Identifier Changes\n- Preserve existing identifiers:\n  - `homeTabRoot`, `wakeTabRoot`, `profileTabRoot`.\n  - Wake flow IDs: `wakeAddAlarmButton`, `wakeAlarmNameField`, `wakeAlarmTimePicker`, `wakeStrictnessPicker`, `wakeFirstTaskField`, `wakeAlarmSaveButton`, `wakeAlarmCancelButton`, `wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeStartRunButton-*`, `wakeEditAlarmButton-*`, `wakeMissionButton-*`, `wakeDismissAlarmButton`, `wakeCompleteWakeCheckButton`, `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton`, `wakeRunStateText`, `wakeReliabilityRow-*`, `wakeReliabilityEscalatedBadge`, `wakeReliabilityEmptyText`.\n  - Paywall/subscription IDs: `paywallSubscribeButton`, `paywallRestoreButton`, `paywallErrorBanner`, `restorePurchasesButton`, `settingsRestorePurchasesButton`.\n- Add identifiers:\n  - Onboarding: `onboardingStepProgress`, `onboardingContinueButton`, `onboardingBackButton`, `onboardingSkipButton`, `onboardingStrictnessInfoButton`.\n  - Home: `homeNextCommitmentCard`, `homePrimaryActionButton`, `homeViewAllTasksButton`, `homeHistoryPreviewButton`, `homeEmptyCreateWakeButton`, `homeSyncErrorBanner`.\n  - List/history/completion/profile: `wakeReadinessTonightSection`, `wakeReadinessLaterSection`, `wakeReadinessPausedSection`, `wakeHistoryTrendSummary`, `wakeHistoryRepairAction`, `wakeCompletionPrimaryNextAction`, `wakeCompletionRecoveryAction`, `profileMissionControlsSection`, `profilePreferencesSection`, `profileAccountBillingSection`, `profileHelpLegalSection`.\n  - Paywall: `paywallPlanOption-*`, `paywallMaybeLaterButton`, `paywallCloseButton`.\n- Rename strategy:\n  - Keep existing IDs as aliases for one release where feasible, then migrate tests to new IDs and remove aliases after CI/Appium parity passes.\n  - Avoid renaming dynamic prefix IDs (`wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeMissionButton-*`) to keep exploratory selectors stable.\n- Automation discoverability guarantees:\n  - Buttons/tabs: explicit stable IDs + visible labels.\n  - Cells/rows: prefix-based IDs for generated items.\n  - Navigation controls: dedicated IDs for back/close/sheet dismiss.\n  - Paywall actions: explicit subscribe/restore/close/maybe-later IDs.\n  - Task actions: one ID per dominant and fallback action in active/completion states.\n\n## Phase Breakdown\n- `visual-system`\n  - Scope: map `screen-spec` semantics to DS tokens/components, define calm-accountability component set, and lock accessibility defaults.\n  - Deliverables: token mapping doc + reusable components + previews for light/dark/Dynamic Type.\n  - Exit tests: DesignSystem token/component tests + snapshot updates pass.\n- `screen-flows`\n  - Scope: apply component system to each target screen in app-shell and paywall paths without changing auth/payments/network/storage architecture.\n  - Deliverables: onboarding/home/list/create-edit/active/completion/history/profile/paywall UI updates with preserved behavior contracts.\n  - Exit tests: updated unit/UI/paywall tests pass; Appium exploratory test passes with migrated IDs.\n- `ux-quality-review`\n  - Scope: hosted iOS screenshot capture, contrast/VoiceOver/Dynamic Type/reduced-motion checks, and regression triage.\n  - Deliverables: before/after screenshot manifest, UX validation notes, and postmortem learning capture artifact.\n  - Exit tests: screenshot-manifest gate + accessibility checklist + acceptance criteria signoff.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- All 9 screen IDs from `screen-spec.json` are implemented and mapped to production SwiftUI surfaces.\n- One-primary-action rule is met on wake-critical surfaces (`active_task`, `completion`) with visible fallback path.\n- Required empty/loading/error/success states are present and stable in layout.\n- Localization keys exist for new user-facing copy in at least `en` and `es` resources.\n- Existing protected systems remain unchanged in behavior: auth, payments, entitlement, networking, storage, localization infrastructure, bundle/release config.\n- UITest/Appium selectors remain discoverable and CI-stable after identifier migration.\n- Hosted iOS validation produces required before/after screenshot states, including Dynamic Type and dark mode.\n- No competitor asset/copy/layout cloning in final UI.\n\n## Explicit Non-Goals\n- No auth rebuild.\n- No payment rebuild.\n- No networking/storage rewrite.\n- No bundle ID changes.\n- No copied competitor assets.\n- No replacement of LaunchRouter auth/onboarding decision model.\n- No changes to RevenueCat wiring or entitlement logic.\n- No schema/storage migration for this phase unless approved by later ADR.\n- No release pipeline or signing configuration changes.\n\n## Risks\n- Identifier churn can break existing UI/Appium scripts if alias window is skipped.\n- Current worker lacks simulator tooling (`xcrun`), so visual verification must run in hosted iOS environment.\n- `PaywallFlowUITests` currently include brittle label-based queries and outdated \"Settings\" tab assumptions; these can cause false negatives during IA updates.\n- Extracting new reusable components may introduce token drift if DS wrappers are not centralized early.\n- History reason-coding depth may exceed current run-event semantics and require phased UI-only representation first.\n\n## No Secret Output\nNo secrets included. If encountered in any source: `secret material omitted`.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'cat .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md'","aggregated_output":"# UX Screen Spec\n## Winning Direction Summary\n- Winning direction: `calm_accountability_direction`.\n- Product emotion: grounded first impression, low-friction wake execution, steady recovery after misses.\n- Core posture: one primary action per screen in wake-critical moments; progressive disclosure for complexity.\n- Monetization stance: free core wake loop remains intact; premium adds reliability tools and deeper insights only.\n- No-clone boundary: adapt interaction principles only; do not replicate external visual/copy/motion signatures.\n\n## Global Visual System\n- Visual principles: medium-compact density on home/list, low density on active/completion, neutral surfaces, strong text contrast.\n- Accent usage: calm blue-green accent reserved for commitment actions and positive confirmations.\n- State signaling: hierarchy, text, and iconography first; color never the sole signal.\n- Semantic tokens:\n  - `color.bg.primary`, `color.bg.secondary`, `color.surface.card`\n  - `color.text.primary`, `color.text.secondary`, `color.text.muted`\n  - `color.action.primary`, `color.action.primaryPressed`, `color.action.secondary`\n  - `color.state.success`, `color.state.warning`, `color.state.destructive`, `color.state.disabled`\n  - `color.state.focusRing`, `color.state.highContrastBorder`\n- Typography: Dynamic Type semantic styles only, multiline-safe labels, tabular numerals for timers/streak counts.\n- Motion: restrained transitions; reduced-motion path uses crossfades/static swaps; no looping urgency animations.\n\n## Global Accessibility Requirements\n- VoiceOver: explicit labels and verbs for every status chip, state banner, and primary CTA.\n- Focus order: top-down, action-first in wake-critical screens, with fallback action immediately after primary CTA.\n- Dynamic Type: no fixed-size text on critical surfaces; multiline expansion with stable card/container growth.\n- Contrast: WCAG-safe text/background and chip/border contrast in light, dark, and high-contrast modes.\n- Reduced motion: every animated transition has non-motion equivalent with equal semantic clarity.\n- Haptic alternatives: all success/warning/failure signals also shown via visible text/icon state.\n- Target sizes: interactive targets at least 44x44pt.\n- One-handed reach: primary wake CTA within lower-thumb zone on large devices.\n\n## Screens\n### onboarding\n- Purpose: establish wake intent, default timing, and optional strictness with reversible setup.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Step progress and intent headline\n  - Current step controls (intent, schedule, strictness)\n  - Primary CTA (`Continue`/`Finish setup`)\n  - Secondary controls (`Skip for now`, `Back`)\n- Primary action: advance setup with explicit confirmation of current choice.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Skip for now` in top-right or bottom secondary button\n  - `Back` in nav bar\n  - `Learn more` inline disclosure for strictness terms\n- Empty state: default recommendation cards (e.g., “Weekday wake at 7:00 AM”) with editable values.\n- Loading state: skeleton for step card and CTA; reserved space for helper text to prevent layout jump.\n- Error state: inline validation and retry message (e.g., schedule save failed) with preserved form values.\n- Copy direction: calm, factual, supportive (“Set your first wake commitment”); avoid guilt or pressure phrases; keep labels short for localization expansion.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces step count and current selection.\n  - Focus order: title -> step controls -> primary CTA -> secondary actions.\n  - Dynamic Type keeps step body multiline without truncating CTA labels.\n  - Reduced motion removes step-slide animation.\n  - One-handed safe: primary CTA anchored near bottom.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Primary CTA visible without scrolling.\n  - Step title and CTA not truncated at common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Skip path visible and clearly secondary.\n  - Light/dark screenshots preserve readable hierarchy and non-color state cues.\n  - Loading and error variants keep card and CTA positions stable.\n\n### home\n- Purpose: show the next wake commitment and provide immediate path to prepare or start.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - `Next Wake Commitment` module\n  - Commitment status line and time context\n  - Primary CTA (`Review wake` or `Start when due`)\n  - Secondary modules (history preview, profile shortcut)\n- Primary action: open the next wake commitment flow.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `View all tasks` link below commitment card\n  - `History` preview tap target\n  - Profile/settings icon in top-right\n- Empty state: “No wake commitments yet” with `Create your first wake` CTA.\n- Loading state: skeleton commitment card with fixed-height placeholder for status text and CTA.\n- Error state: sync/load failure banner with `Retry` and last-known commitment snapshot.\n- Copy direction: operational clarity (“Next wake: Tomorrow 7:00 AM”); avoid vague motivation-only copy; localizable date/time formats.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver reads commitment title, due time, and state in one coherent phrase.\n  - Focus order prioritizes commitment card and primary CTA before analytics tiles.\n  - Dynamic Type wraps status line and keeps CTA fully readable.\n  - Contrast-safe status chips with text labels/icons.\n  - One-handed reach keeps primary card action in thumb zone.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Next commitment card is first visible module.\n  - Primary CTA visible without scroll.\n  - Status is understandable without relying on color alone.\n  - No critical text truncation on common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Light/dark mode screenshots preserve legibility and hierarchy.\n\n### primary_list\n- Purpose: manage all wake tasks grouped by readiness for quick scanning and resume.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Readiness sections (`Tonight`, `Later`, `Paused`)\n  - Task rows with time, status chip, and quick action\n  - Primary list CTA (`Create wake task`)\n  - Filters/sort as secondary controls\n- Primary action: resume or open the most relevant task in readiness groups.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Pause/Resume` swipe or row action\n  - `Edit` from row overflow\n  - `Filter` control in header\n- Empty state: sectioned guidance with `Create wake task` CTA and short explanation of readiness groups.\n- Loading state: section headers and row skeletons with stable row height.\n- Error state: inline section error with retry; unaffected sections remain visible.\n- Copy direction: plain labels (“Paused”, “Tonight”), no novelty jargon; avoid punitive miss language; ensure short translatable chips.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces section + task + state + available action.\n  - Focus order follows section header then rows.\n  - Dynamic Type allows multiline task titles and wraps metadata.\n  - 44x44pt minimum for row actions and overflow menu.\n  - Non-haptic cues for pause/resume confirmation.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Readiness sections visibly distinct by headings, not color only.\n  - At least one row shows clear status chip text/icon.\n  - Primary create CTA visible without scroll in empty state.\n  - Dynamic Type does not clip row action labels.\n  - Loading/error states preserve row geometry.\n\n### create/edit\n- Purpose: author or revise a wake task through linear, low-cognitive configuration.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Step sequence (`Intent -> Timing -> Safeguards -> Review`)\n  - Current step fields\n  - Primary CTA (`Continue`/`Save wake task`)\n  - Secondary actions (`Cancel`, `Advanced options`)\n- Primary action: complete current step and move forward to final save.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Advanced options` disclosure below core fields\n  - `Cancel` in nav bar\n  - `Back` to previous step\n- Empty state: prefilled starter values with concise explanations and defaults.\n- Loading state: form section skeletons with preserved field spacing and fixed footer CTA area.\n- Error state: inline field errors and top summary for save/sync failure with retry.\n- Copy direction: explicit and instructional (“Choose your wake window”); avoid legalistic or alarmist phrasing; localize numeric/time units cleanly.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver reads field label, value, and validation state.\n  - Focus order is step header -> fields -> primary CTA -> secondary actions.\n  - Dynamic Type allows multiline helper text and non-overlapping controls.\n  - Reduced motion disables animated step transitions.\n  - One-handed reach keeps primary CTA in bottom action bar.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Current step and progress context clearly visible.\n  - Primary CTA visible without scrolling on each step.\n  - Error screenshot shows preserved input and clear correction guidance.\n  - No truncation of key field labels at common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Layout stability between loading and filled states.\n\n### active_task\n- Purpose: execute a live wake commitment with one dominant action and explicit state.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Current-state banner (e.g., `Wake Check In Progress`)\n  - Dominant primary CTA (`I'm awake` or equivalent state action)\n  - Fallback action (clearly labeled, lower emphasis)\n  - Minimal contextual details/timer\n- Primary action: confirm wake completion step for current state.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Need extra minute` fallback button below primary CTA\n  - `View details` collapsed disclosure\n- Empty state: not applicable; if no active task, redirect to home with explanatory message.\n- Loading state: state banner and disabled CTA placeholders while status sync resolves.\n- Error state: explicit sync/permission failure banner with retry and safe fallback path.\n- Copy direction: short imperative clarity (“Confirm you’re awake”); avoid shaming, urgency theatrics, or dense text; localization-safe verbs.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces current state before actionable controls.\n  - Focus order: state banner -> primary CTA -> fallback -> details.\n  - High contrast for primary action and state text in both themes.\n  - Reduced motion removes transition flourishes; state updates remain textual.\n  - Primary CTA 44x44pt minimum and thumb reachable.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Exactly one visually dominant primary action.\n  - Fallback action is visible and clearly secondary.\n  - State is understandable without motion or color-only cues.\n  - Dark/light screenshots both show clear CTA contrast.\n  - Loading/error variants keep CTA and banner positions stable.\n\n### completion\n- Purpose: confirm outcome, reinforce continuity, and route to one next-best action.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Completion confirmation message\n  - Outcome summary (time/status)\n  - Primary next action (`Set next wake` or `Quick reflection`)\n  - Secondary repair/help actions\n- Primary action: choose the recommended next step to sustain continuity.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `View history` link\n  - `Repair missed wake` when relevant\n  - Dismiss/back to home\n- Empty state: if opened without prior task, show neutral guidance and `Go to home` CTA.\n- Loading state: confirmation card skeleton with reserved next-action button space.\n- Error state: failure saving completion/notes shows retry with preserved summary.\n- Copy direction: respectful, factual (“Wake completed at 7:02 AM”); avoid celebratory pressure or guilt; keep concise localizable phrasing.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces completion state and next action recommendation.\n  - Focus order prioritizes next action before tertiary links.\n  - Dynamic Type keeps summary and CTA multiline-safe.\n  - Non-color indicators for success/recovery states.\n  - Haptic confirmation always paired with text/icon confirmation.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Confirmation state is immediately visible above fold.\n  - Primary next action visible without scroll.\n  - Recovery path present for missed/partial outcomes without punitive copy.\n  - No key truncation in common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Visual structure stable across loading/error states.\n\n### history/streaks\n- Purpose: show reliability trend, explain outcome reasons, and enable repair planning.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Reliability summary/trend module\n  - Reason-coded entries (`completed`, `missed`, `recovered`)\n  - Primary CTA (`Plan repair` when needed or `Set next wake`)\n  - Secondary filters/time-range controls\n- Primary action: initiate repair planning or next wake setup from current reliability context.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - Time-range segmented control\n  - Entry detail drill-in\n  - Export/share if available as tertiary\n- Empty state: no history yet message with `Complete your first wake` guidance.\n- Loading state: chart/list skeletons with fixed axes/header footprint to avoid jump.\n- Error state: partial data notice with retry; stale cached entries remain visible.\n- Copy direction: explanatory accountability (“Missed: alarm silenced early”); avoid blame language; keep reason labels short and translatable.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver reads trend direction and each entry reason as text.\n  - Focus order: summary -> primary CTA -> entries -> filters.\n  - Dynamic Type supports multiline reason text and chip expansion.\n  - Charts/rings must have text equivalents.\n  - One-handed reach for primary repair CTA.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Reason-coded outcomes visible as text, not color alone.\n  - Primary action visible without scroll in relevant state.\n  - Trend remains legible in light/dark modes.\n  - Dynamic Type does not clip reason labels.\n  - Loading/error maintain stable chart/list containers.\n\n### profile/settings\n- Purpose: separate mission controls from preferences, billing, and legal/support.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Mission Controls section\n  - Preferences section\n  - Account/Billing section\n  - Help/Legal section\n- Primary action: access mission-critical settings quickly and safely.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - Manage subscription within Account/Billing\n  - Help/contact actions in Help/Legal\n  - Sign out/delete account as guarded destructive flows\n- Empty state: account-not-synced state with sign-in/retry prompt and local settings access.\n- Loading state: section skeleton rows with fixed grouping spacing.\n- Error state: account/billing fetch error inline with retry; mission settings remain accessible.\n- Copy direction: plain and specific section labels; avoid mixing legal/account terms with wake execution labels; localization-safe row titles.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces section boundaries and row purpose.\n  - Focus order follows section order, mission-first.\n  - Dynamic Type allows multiline row labels and subtitles.\n  - Destructive actions include explicit text/icon confirmation.\n  - Touch targets for rows and toggles meet minimum size.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Section separation is visually obvious.\n  - Mission Controls appears above Account/Billing and Help/Legal.\n  - No truncation of section headers or row labels at common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Error state does not hide mission-critical settings.\n  - No competitor-like cloned settings composition.\n\n### paywall/subscription\n- Purpose: explain premium reliability value clearly while preserving trust and free-core continuity.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Value summary (free vs premium)\n  - Premium feature list (advanced safeguards, deeper analytics, adaptive planning)\n  - Primary CTA (`Start trial`/`Upgrade`)\n  - Secondary actions (`Not now`, `Restore purchases`, `Manage plans`)\n- Primary action: start subscription only after clear value comparison.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Not now` visible and equally discoverable\n  - `Restore purchases` near plan controls\n  - `Manage plans` link for transparency\n- Empty state: entitlement unknown shows neutral explainer and loading indicator.\n- Loading state: plan cards skeleton with fixed CTA/footer positions.\n- Error state: purchase/restore failure with explicit retry and non-blocking exit.\n- Copy direction: transparent, non-coercive (“Free includes core wake flow”); avoid fake scarcity/countdowns or shaming declines; localize pricing and term cadence.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver clearly distinguishes free and premium benefits.\n  - Focus order: value summary -> plans -> primary CTA -> decline/restore actions.\n  - Dynamic Type keeps plan details readable without clipping price text.\n  - Color-independent plan selection indicators.\n  - Reduced motion disables animated plan emphasis.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Free and premium value are clearly separated in text.\n  - Close/decline action is visible and not obscured.\n  - Primary CTA visible without scrolling on standard iPhone viewport.\n  - Loading/error states preserve card and CTA layout stability.\n  - Screen does not mimic a named competitor’s composition, copy, or visual motif.\n\n## Screenshot Acceptance Checklist\n- Primary action is visible above the fold on each required screen.\n- Common Dynamic Type sizes do not truncate critical labels/CTAs except explicitly documented non-critical text.\n- Core status remains understandable in both light and dark mode screenshots.\n- State communication does not rely on color alone.\n- Loading and error variants preserve layout stability and element placement.\n- Paywall clearly separates free and premium value with transparent decline/restore actions.\n- No screen visually clones competitor/reference compositions, branded motifs, or proprietary interaction framing.\n\n## No-Clone Statement\nThese specs adapt abstract UX patterns only and do not copy another app’s assets, copy, brand, visual composition, screenshots, or proprietary interaction sequences.\n\n## No Secret Output\nNo credentials, session tokens, private links, signed URLs, cookies, API keys, or user secrets are included. If encountered in source material: `secret material omitted`.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
