on`, `WakeEmptyStateView`, `WakeLoadingStateView`, `WakeErrorStateView`, `WakePremiumCallout`, and `WakeCompletionFeedback` updated as reusable primitives (not one-off screen styling).\n- Typography wrappers with Dynamic Type support: added `WakeTypography.lineLimit(for:)` and `wakeType(...)` wrapper for multiline-safe semantic text application; components now use these wrappers for critical labels/messages.\n- Cards/rows/progress-status alignment: component set directly covers card, row, chip, progress/status, primary/secondary actions, empty/loading/error, premium callout, and completion feedback from selected direction.\n- VoiceOver/accessibility helpers: component-level accessibility labels/hints/traits/focus priority/minimum target usage added or refined (row combined summaries, state announcements, action hints, focus priorities).\n- State coverage in previews/tests: preview states include empty/loading/error/active/completion/premium and dynamic-type + dark mode + increased contrast variant; token tests updated for newly added semantic values.\n- Existing behavior preserved: changes scoped to DesignSystem visual primitives and tests only; no auth/payment/entitlement/networking/storage/navigation/bundle behavior changes.\n- Verifier notes remain pending and not self-approved.\n\n## Component inventory\n- Tokens:\n  - `WakeColorTokens` semantic state and contrast additions\n  - `WakeTypography` line-limit helper for Dynamic Type-safe multiline behavior\n  - `WakeSpacing.divider` and `wakeType(...)` view wrapper\n- Reusable components:\n  - `WakeCard`\n  - `WakeRow`\n  - `WakeStatusChip`\n  - `WakeProgressStatus`\n  - `WakePrimaryActionButton`\n  - `WakeSecondaryActionButton`\n  - `WakeEmptyStateView`\n  - `WakeLoadingStateView`\n  - `WakeErrorStateView`\n  - `WakePremiumCallout`\n  - `WakeCompletionFeedback`\n\n## Accessibility notes\n- Minimum hit-target support at component-level via `wakeMinimumTapTarget()` and 44pt min heights.\n- Focus-order support through `wakeFocusPriority(...)` on primary/secondary actions.\n- VoiceOver summaries/hints added for row and stateful components.\n- Progress and state semantics provide text equivalents (not color-only cues).\n- Reduce-motion path respected by avoiding reliance on animated-only meaning and using stable textual state.\n\n## Screenshot states prepared\n- Previews prepared for:\n  - default mixed component system state\n  - dynamic type + dark mode completion state\n  - active task high-contrast state with primary/fallback actions\n  - loading state\n  - error state\n  - empty state\n  - completion feedback state\n  - premium callout state\n\n## Risks\n- Known deferred: runtime visual verification and snapshot generation require the hosted macOS/iOS quality gate because the Daytona worker has no Swift toolchain.\n- Known deferred: high-contrast and Dynamic Type runtime execution remains assigned to the hosted macOS/iOS quality gate.\n- Known deferred: localization-specific long-string clipping requires hosted screenshot verification in target locales.\n\n## Verifier notes\n- Accepted by independent verifier: reviewed design-system token/component changes (`WakeVisualTokens.swift`, `WakeVisualComponents.swift`, `WakeAccessibility.swift`), tests (`WakeVisualSystemTests.swift`), and previews; implementation is scoped to `visual-system` only (no auth/payment/networking/storage/navigation/bundle flow changes), with runtime verification pending in hosted iOS validation.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
